Ignatius detected enemy fire from long range. The eagle went into a
powerdive avoiding the shots. &quot;So that&#39;s the game. I&#39;ll teach them my
rules.&quot; he fired two wing missles at Attila and five bursts from his eyes at
Luzbel. He stayed close to the water trying to use the water to confuse the
sensors. He knew that the closer he got the more likely he&#39;d be detected and
attacked.

The call to retreat came through from Slayer. &quot;We can&#39;t retreat yet, I&#39;m
barely warmed up.&quot; he wanted to rescue the leader even though he knew that
Prebon had made a strategic mistake (To put it lightly) attacking the Iron
fist. He vowed allegiance to his leader and intended to follow it through to
the end.

Long range scanners showed Slayer going the opposite direction. He switched
frequencies and called Slayer again. &quot;Lead them back toward me, I&#39;ll lay
down coverfire.&quot; Ignatius wasn&#39;t facing fire from the fortress so he knew
that he was out of range. He transformed to robot mode and dove into the
water. he set all operating functions on minimal hoping thier attension
would remain on Slayer.
